                        "created_at": "1716079991",
                        "id": "18030602212952607",
                        "text": "Have you ever seen a wagyu fat-fried cheeseburger? \ud83c\udf54\n\n\u5143\u7956\u306e\u5207\u3063\u305f\u3084\u3064\u306f\u6771\u4eac\u306b\u6765\u305f\uff01\n\n@briskstand_asakusa is the first Tokyo location of the famous Kobe burger joint known for their original way of cooking cheeseburgers. 100% domestic Japanese beef is topped with caramelized onions and cheese before being cut in half, and then cooked again in its own fat, creating a crispy, burnt inside packed with all kinds of umami.\n\n\ud83c\udff7\ufe0f \u00a52350 \u5207\u3063\u305f\u3084\u3064\u30c0\u30d6\u30eb\u30d1\u30c6\u30a3 Sliced Double Patty Burger\n\n\ud83d\udccd BRISKSTAND ASAKUSA\uff08\u30d6\u30ea\u30b9\u30af\u30b9\u30bf\u30f3\u30c9\u30a2\u30b5\u30af\u30b5\uff09 (2 Chome-9-16 Kotobuki, Taito City, Tokyo 111-0042, Japan)\n\n#PR #wagyu #burger #tokyoeats #tokyofood #\u6771\u4eac\u30b0\u30eb\u30e1"
                    }
                }
